## D. Script court de collecte standard

```powershell
$Ticket  = "1697121"
$JobName = "MP_ESXI - backup copy vers NAS02 NO TICKET"
$OutDir  = "C:\Temp\Veeam_$Ticket"

New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $OutDir -Force | Out-Null

if (Get-Module -ListAvailable -Name Veeam.Backup.PowerShell) {
    Import-Module Veeam.Backup.PowerShell
}
elseif (Get-PSSnapin -Registered | Where-Object { $_.Name -eq "VeeamPSSnapIn" }) {
    Add-PSSnapin VeeamPSSnapIn
}
else {
    throw "Impossible de charger les cmdlets Veeam."
}

$Job = Get-VBRBackupCopyJob -Name $JobName
if (-not $Job) {
    throw "Job introuvable : $JobName"
}

$Job | Format-List * | Out-File "$OutDir\01_Job.txt" -Encoding utf8

$Sessions = Get-VBRBackupSession | Where-Object {
    $_.JobName -eq $JobName
} | Sort-Object EndTimeUTC -Descending

$Sessions | Select-Object -First 20 `
    Name, JobName, CreationTime, EndTime, State, Result |
    Export-Csv "$OutDir\02_Sessions.csv" -NoTypeInformation -Encoding utf8

$LastSession = $Sessions | Select-Object -First 1
if ($LastSession) {
    $LastSession | Format-List * | Out-File "$OutDir\03_LastSession.txt" -Encoding utf8
}
else {
    "Aucune session trouvée pour ce job." | Out-File "$OutDir\03_LastSession.txt" -Encoding utf8
}

Write-Host "Collecte terminée : $OutDir"
```

### Résultat utile

Ce script a bien généré :

* `01_Job.txt`
* `02_Sessions.csv`
* `03_LastSession.txt`

### Intérêt

C’est un bon **script de collecte de base**, sûr et exploitable pour un diagnostic initial.

